## Code

<!-- livebook:{"reevaluate_automatically":true} -->

```elixir
defmodule Checker do
  def lookup_dist(data, city2index, from, to) do
    from = Map.get(city2index, from)
    to = Map.get(city2index, to)
    data
    |> Enum.at(from)
    |> Enum.at(to)
  end
  
  def check(data, city2index, sequence) do
    [Enum.at(sequence, -1)|sequence]
    |> Enum.chunk_every(2, 1, :discard)
    |> Enum.reduce(0, fn [from, to], acc -> acc + lookup_dist(data, city2index, from, to) end)
  end
end
```

## User Interface

<!-- livebook:{"reevaluate_automatically":true} -->

```elixir
kino = Kino.Input.textarea("Sequence:", default: default_sequence)
```

<!-- livebook:{"reevaluate_automatically":true} -->

```elixir
sequence =
  kino
  |> Kino.Input.read()
  |> String.split("\n")
  |> Enum.map(&String.trim/1)
  |> Enum.filter(fn entry -> entry != "" end)
```

<!-- livebook:{"reevaluate_automatically":true} -->

```elixir
Checker.check(data, city2index, sequence)
```

And that is the distance of the sequence!
